Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.59,0:07:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, you've picked a fine time to-
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.88,0:07:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Weiss] Not another word.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.30,0:07:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We're coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.84,0:07:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Whitley] Things are already bad enough
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.34,0:07:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,after what you did to father.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.93,0:07:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you want us to harbor fugitives too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.51,0:07:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Our family has a reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.72,0:07:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's what you're worried\Nabout? Your reputation?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.76,0:07:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm just saying
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.59,0:07:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that we've already lost\Nall the house staff,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.59,0:07:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and mother locked herself in her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.43,0:07:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- Maybe you haven't figured\Nout what's going on, Whitley,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.64,0:08:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but we're busy trying to save Atlas.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.88,0:08:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- Look. Our friend is hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.63,0:08:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We just need a place to\Nlay low while she rests,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.09,0:08:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we'll be out of your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.22,0:08:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- Fine. What do you expect me to do then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.43,0:08:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- Go to your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.38,0:08:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.01,0:08:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ruby?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.93,0:08:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- I hope everyone's doing all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.76,0:08:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- If you're worried
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.59,0:08:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,about Yang, you could\Nalways try calling her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.80,0:08:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- But that's the thing. I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.01,0:08:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jaune] I repeat, if anybody can hear me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.88,0:08:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We need transport back to Mantle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.26,0:08:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Yang] We need to get out of this weather
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.39,0:08:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,before the cold drops\Nour Auras completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.63,0:08:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How much farther to the outpost?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.01,0:09:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ren? How much-\N- I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.38,0:09:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- I thought you said you saw\Nit when you were up in the air?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.63,0:09:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- I did. Before I had to cut\Nmyself loose to help you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.05,0:09:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah. You've brought\Nthat up a couple times now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.43,0:09:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Something you need to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.81,0:09:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- Not really. Wouldn't want\Nto waste any more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.18,0:09:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey, what is your deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.64,0:09:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.63,0:09:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- Well, I'm sorry things\Naren't going smoothly enough
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.38,0:09:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,for you.\N- Guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.38,0:09:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- They're not going smoothly at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.18,0:09:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- I hate to break it to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.18,0:09:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,but that's part of being a Huntsman.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.81,0:09:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- Are you kidding?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.63,0:09:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't know the first\Nthing about being Huntsmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.63,0:09:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We clearly weren't ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.88,0:09:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,- Guys, stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.09,0:09:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- Were we not ready when we saved Haven,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.01,0:09:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,when we took down a Leviathan?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.84,0:09:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We got the lamp to Atlas.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.43,0:09:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- And then we lost it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.68,0:09:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And after that, when we had
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.93,0:09:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to make real decisions, we\Ngot every single one wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.72,0:09:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm not going to pretend like\Nwe did everything perfectly,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.51,0:10:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,but if we'd done nothing,\Nthings would be even worse
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.84,0:10:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,than they are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.68,0:10:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- How could they possibly be worse?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.10,0:10:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We are stuck out here while\NSalem has the lamp and Oscar.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.05,0:10:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got no plan, no army.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.63,0:10:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- We've got the Maiden.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.88,0:10:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- And by keeping her\Nfrom opening the vault
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.30,0:10:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,for Ironwood, we're just trapping\Nthe whole city, for Salem.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.05,0:10:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,People are going to die, because of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.26,0:10:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- So what? We should just\Ngive Ironwood what he wants?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.14,0:10:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Abandon Mantle?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.38,0:10:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You think Atlas is still\Ngoing to be able to float
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.34,0:10:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to safety now that she's here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.63,0:10:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.47,0:10:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But these aren't the kinds of\Ndecisions we should be making
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.47,0:10:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because we have no idea what we're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.05,0:10:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Jaune] Okay. Both of you, cut it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.30,0:10:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm just saying what\Nnobody else wants to.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.76,0:10:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We are in way over our heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.01,0:10:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruby is barely more than\Na kid, I'm just an orphan
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.30,0:10:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,from the middle of nowhere-
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.22,0:10:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ren, I-\N- You cheated your way
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.60,0:10:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,into Beacon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.13,0:10:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- You don't think we\Nshould be Huntsmen? Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.93,0:10:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm getting out of the cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.63,0:10:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Still gotta job to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.38,0:11:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- Seriously, is your goal\Njust to push everyone away?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.34,0:11:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Ozpin] Oscar?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.13,0:11:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't panic. We're going to be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.63,0:11:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Oscar] What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.88,0:11:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Salem] My long lost Ozma.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.30,0:11:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Found, at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.97,0:11:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So small this new host of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.51,0:11:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a wonder my hound didn't break you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.68,0:11:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been how many years\Nsince we saw each other
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.51,0:11:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,like this, face to face?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.26,0:11:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And nothing to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.26,0:11:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm sorry the reunion isn't living up
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.55,0:11:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to your expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.09,0:12:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- You can pretend boy,\Nbut you're not fully him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.63,0:12:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.55,0:12:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, perhaps you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.84,0:12:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and I can have a better\Nworking relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.26,0:12:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oscar, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.43,0:12:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The Beacon Relic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.26,0:12:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,My forces have been unable
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.59,0:12:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to locate the relic beneath the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.30,0:12:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If I know my Ozma, he has\Nused some means of deception
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.22,0:12:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to hide its location\Ndifferently than the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.76,0:12:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to know where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.26,0:12:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- I...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.84,0:12:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not something I know about.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.09,0:12:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- Of course, you would\Nkeep that one guarded
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.13,0:12:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.68,0:12:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How about something easier, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.93,0:12:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The password for the lamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.80,0:12:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- The lamp is all out of questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.13,0:13:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- The lies come out of you so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.22,0:13:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Like-minded souls indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.18,0:13:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,One of you is going to\Ntell me what you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.85,0:13:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't much care if it is you, or Ozma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.09,0:13:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, I'll finally have the relic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.76,0:13:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- I won't tell you anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.30,0:13:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.18,0:13:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hazel?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.80,0:13:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.30,0:13:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Hazel] That was for Haven Academy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.18,0:14:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that follows,\Nwill be from my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.38,0:14:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- Your grace, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.34,0:14:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What, is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.22,0:14:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- An experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.22,0:14:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So far I am pleased with the results.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.18,0:14:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you need something Cinder?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.06,0:14:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes. I, I want to search\Nfor the Winter Maiden.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.84,0:14:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I think-\N- Do you hear that my pet?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.63,0:14:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,She thinks. She wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.26,0:14:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As if she's done something
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.68,0:14:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that warrants me caring\Nabout either of those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.47,0:14:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- We're just sitting and waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.80,0:14:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the Maiden Power,\Nthe vault means nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.72,0:14:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me claim it for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.22,0:14:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- I will tell you when\Nand where you are needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.35,0:14:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- But your grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.80,0:14:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'd like to think I have\Nshown a great deal of patience
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.59,0:15:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,over my many years walking remnant...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.26,0:15:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but I do hate repeating myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.55,0:15:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You will remain here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.55,0:15:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.76,0:15:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.72,0:15:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.18,0:15:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Without you, I am nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.34,0:15:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.80,0:15:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want to check on something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.55,0:15:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be back before anyone realizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.22,0:15:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to see if anything\Nis still going on
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.22,0:15:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,at Amity Colosseum.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.80,0:15:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Salem doesn't know those\Nchildren like I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.38,0:15:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They wouldn't just abandon\Ntheir misguided attempt
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.13,0:15:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to save the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.63,0:15:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- [Emerald] If she doesn't want to, I'll come.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.43,0:16:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been working on my Semblance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.39,0:16:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I can help.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.30,0:16:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't tell anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.80,0:16:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- (grunts) How much did you overhear?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.01,0:16:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're right Ren. I..
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.22,0:16:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I did cheat my way into Beacon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.80,0:16:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm glad I had people\Naround me to help me see
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.01,0:16:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that, I was bigger than that mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.30,0:16:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got people around you too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.34,0:16:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to force\Nyourself to be strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.51,0:16:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The more you hide
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.34,0:16:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,from what you're feeling,\Nthe more alone you're going
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.51,0:16:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.22,0:16:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.30,0:16:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- If anyone cares, I found\Na part to fix the bike.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.13,0:16:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.80,0:16:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.84,0:17:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,For what it's worth, I'm\Nsorry he said that to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.88,0:17:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you've had to work\Nhard to get here Jaune.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.34,0:17:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- We're all under a lot\Nof stress right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.84,0:17:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to push people away too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.93,0:17:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- Do you think she thinks less of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.97,0:17:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,for not helping out with Amity?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.93,0:17:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ruby is your sister. She's\Nalways going to love you,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.89,0:17:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,even if you disagree with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.13,0:17:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.80,0:17:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Ruby.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.97,0:17:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,- I need to get some sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.97,0:17:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but, I can't stop thinking about Oscar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.80,0:17:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,- Go on. I'll make sure\NRen doesn't brute himself
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.80,0:17:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to death out in the cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.63,0:17:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,- Thanks. I just have a bad feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.38,0:17:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Things always seem to get\Nworse before they get better.
